**9. Build Readiness Summary**

All five streams have completed Phase 2 (Independent Exploration) and
passed convergence review. Status as of CR-2:

**Completed:**

• 52 business rules translated to YAML with 257 inline test cases

• All 4 demo case hand calculations complete (Cases 1, 2, 3, 4)

• Calculation trace format defined and validated against Case 1

• All 3 cross-stream conflicts resolved (CRITICAL-002)

• All 7 S2-blocking cross-stream items resolved

• Legacy schema DDL with intentional realism patterns

• Domain entity model with computed fields and data quality flags

• OpenAPI specs for all 3 services

• Shared type definitions in Go and TypeScript

• Frontend component interfaces and architecture

• Verification strategy with boundary case inventory

**Remaining before BUILD:**

• DISC-01: Update Case 3 hand calc beneficiary name to match fixture

• XS-13: Decide /data-quality/member/{id} endpoint ownership (Connector
vs Intelligence)

• C-12 (Workspace API), C-16 (Composition Rules), C-18 (Integration
Tests) remain Draft --- acceptable for build start, will finalize during
implementation

**20 of 23 contracts are at Proposed or Resolved state. The 3 remaining
Draft contracts are non-blocking for build start. The parallel design
phase is complete.**

**10. Registry Maintenance Protocol**

This registry is maintained exclusively by the Technical Director.
Streams never directly modify this document. During BUILD phase,
contract updates follow the SYNC_LOG protocol with formal revision
through the convergence hub.

A contract cannot override a governing principle, ADR, or statutory
provision. If a contract contradicts a governing document, the governing
document wins and the contract must be revised.
